derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from Anglo-Norman French contributour, from Latin contribut- 'added' (see contribution)

entry.tran: (尤指不愉快事件的)促成因素，原因之一
entry.def: You can use contributor to refer to one of the causes of an event or situation, especially if that event or situation is an unpleasant one.

example.ex: Old buses are major contributors to pollution in British cities...
example.tran: 破旧的公交车是造成英国城市污染的主要因素。

example.ex: All this can lead to divisive family arguments to which guilt is a major contributor.
example.tran: 所有这些都能导致家庭意见不和，而内疚是其中的主要因素。

means.word_mean: 1. someone who contributes (or promises to contribute) a sum of money
2. a writer whose work is published in a newspaper or magazine or as part of a book
